# Problem Definition

## Business Problem
The business aims to proactively identify customers who are likely to churn in order to reduce revenue loss and improve retention strategies.

## Objective
Develop a machine learning model that predicts whether a customer will churn based on historical transaction behavior.

## Target Variable
Churn (Binary):
- 1 = No purchases in the last 180 days
- 0 = Active customer

## Datasets
1. Online Retail Dataset (Kaggle)
   - Contains transactional data including customer purchases, invoice details, and product information.

## Key Features (Planned)
- Recency
- Frequency
- Monetary
- Average Order Value
- Purchase Trend

## Success Metrics
- Accuracy
- Precision
- Recall
- ROC-AUC
